This paper discusses a covert communication method using security cameras and IR light, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques to encode and decode data, which could be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of malware to control the cameras, which could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY).
